      "schema:description": "Alexandre Mury is a Brazilian multidisciplinary artist and independent researcher whose practice investigates the image as cultural infrastructure: a dynamic relational system linking body, memory, archive, document, materiality, circulation, interpretation, and the organization of knowledge.",
      "schema:disambiguatingDescription": "Brazilian multidisciplinary artist and independent researcher, born in 1976 in São Fidélis, Rio de Janeiro, associated with post-conceptual practices, the expanded field of the image, expanded documentation, semantic systems, and the Alexandre Mury Ontology (A.M.O.).",
